The paper discusses the development of a new kernel for support vector machines (SVM) for classification, specifically for semi-supervised learning. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of probabilistic mixture density models and Gaussian mixtures for real-valued input spaces suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of the new kernel with other existing kernels, indicating a focus on computational statistics (cs.SI).
